30
00:02:07.940 --> 00:02:10.980
And it's really high quality, but it's baked.

31
00:02:10.980 --> 00:02:12.840
So it cannot be altered at runtime.

32
00:02:12.840 --> 00:02:17.680
So once you bake it, it takes quite a long time to bake if you're using the CPU.

33
00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:21.460
And then once that's done, you cannot edit it at runtime, which means you can't have

34
00:02:21.460 --> 00:02:28.580
a light swing, for example, and update lighting in real time if you were using a purely static

35
00:02:28.580 --> 00:02:29.580
system.

